[0;35mSECURITY & RELIABILITY PROTOCOLS[0m

Ralph Wiggum Protocol (Loop Prevention):
  вҖў Max 20 iterations on any loop (cargo builds, test retries, API pagination)
  вҖў If fails 20 times: STOP and ask for help (prevents infinite loops)

Anchor Rule (LLM Hallucination Prevention):
  вҖў Update CORE_TYPES_ANCHOR.md after EVERY coding session
  вҖў Contains exact Rust struct definitions and PyO3 bindings
  вҖў Prevents Claude from hallucinating on next session

Checkpoint Rule (Network Resilience):
  вҖў All API operations save state to checkpoint.json
  вҖў Never restart from zero on network failure
  вҖў Resume from last checkpoint on restart

IBKR-Primary Protocol (Data Feed Reliability):
  вҖў IBKR Gateway is primary data source (real-time)
  вҖў yfinance fallback for graceful degradation
  вҖў H-07 auto-reconnection (Docker restart on failures)
  вҖў Telegram alerts on all major transitions

Approval Gate Protocol (User Control):
  вҖў Every phase pauses for explicit approval
  вҖў User can [c]ontinue, [s]kip, or [q]uit
  вҖў All approvals logged to execution journal
  вҖў No automatic progression

EFFORT: ~504 hours development + testing
TIMELINE: ~16 weeks (end of June 2026)
SECURITY: All protocols tested across 52 paper trades in V1
SECURITY: 16 runtime invariants + 4 structural guarantees validated

